hii [C[C[C    Basic commands in linux:
=====================================================
1.pwd - present working directory.
2.touch - to create a empty file.
3.mkdir - to create a directory.
4.ls - it will show the files and directories.
5.cat>file1 - to create a file with in the data.
6.cat file2 - to show the content of a file2
7.cat>>file1 - to add a new line in a file1.
8.cd niki - change niki directory.
9.rm filename 
10.rm -f filename - remove a file.
11.rm -rf - remove a file 		`and directoryin force fully.
12.rmdir dirname - remove a directory.
13.ll - to show the content of a file in longlist formatt.
14.head file name - to show the 1 st 10 lines in a file.
15.tail filename - to show the last  10 lines in a file.
16.tac file name - to show the content of a file in reverse formatted.
17.more file name - to show the content of a file.
18.less file name - to show the content of a file in on page like a manner.
19.cd .. - one directory back.
20.vi .file1 - to create a hidden file.
21.cat>.file1
22.ls -a - to show the hidden files.
23.cat .filename - to show content of a hidden file.
24.cat>>.file - to added a new lines in a content of a file.
25.cp file2.txt file3.txt - copy one file to another file.
26.cp file3.txt /root/balu/nikhil - file3.txt copy to nikhil directory.
27.cp -r apple balu - copy apple directort to balu directory.
28.cp -r apple /root/balu/nikhil - copy apple directory to nikhil directory.
29.mv file2.txt file3.txt - rename and move the file.
30.mv apple /root/balu/nikhil - move apple directory to destination nikhil ddirectory.
31.sort - to see the data in the sorted order
